{"_id":"61894417-ded4-3cc6-ba87-f188536c6d43","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"That would be possible if DoSomething returns a Task that is eventually cancelled. In that case, it's not a \"problem\" with Task.Run; it's working properly. StartNew would just be ignoring the cancellation.\r\n\r\nOn a side note, you should use await instead of ContinueWith. If you use Task.Run with await, then the code would be clearer.","postId":"2013_08_startnew-is-dangerous-4c5e3290-63e6-3320-85d1-3054cbca80ce","replyTo":"d38954ec-2c27-3f54-9071-7f316db7b74f","date":"2016-11-15T14:06:51Z","timestamp":1479218811,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}